## üß© Circuit Schematic (Breadboard Layout) ‚Äî **As specified in the thesis**

The table below follows the wiring described in the thesis (Biometric Health Data Measurement with Live Broadcast). Citations to the thesis are included for each device.

### üì∫ ST7789 TFT Display (ST7789, 240√ó320 / 2.0")
| TFT Pin | ESP32 Pin | Notes |
|--------:|:---------:|:-----|
| VCC     | 3.3V      | Power (3.3V).|
| GND     | GND       | Ground.|
| SCL (SCK) | GPIO 18 | SPI Clock.|
| SDA (MOSI)| GPIO 23 | SPI MOSI / Data.|
| RES     | GPIO 4    | Reset.|
| DC      | GPIO 2    | Data/Command.|
| CS      | GPIO 5    | Chip Select.|
| BLK     | 3.3V (or via resistor/driver) | Backlight (depends on module).|

---

### ‚ù§Ô∏è MAX30100 (Pulse Oximeter)
| MAX30100 Pin | ESP32 Pin | Notes |
|-------------:|:---------:|:-----|
| VIN          | 3.3V      | Power |
| GND          | GND       | Ground.|
| SDA          | GPIO 21   | I2C SDA shared bus.|
| SCL          | GPIO 22   | I2C SCL shared bus.|
| INT          | (Not used) | Optional interrupt ‚Äî leave disconnected unless used.|

---

### üå°Ô∏è MLX90614 (IR Temperature)
| MLX90614 Pin | ESP32 Pin | Notes |
|-------------:|:---------:|:-----|
| VDD / VCC    | **5V** *or* **3.3V** | Thesis wiring uses **5V**; module is specified 3‚Äì5V (check your breakout). If the module's datasheet/breakout requires 5V, use 5V. 
                                        If the breakout supports 3.3V I2C, prefer **3.3V** to keep I2C levels consistent with ESP32.|
| GND          | GND       | Ground.|
| SDA          | GPIO 21   | I2C SDA (shared with MAX30100).|
| SCL          | GPIO 22   | I2C SCL (shared).|

**Important:** The thesis lists **VDD ‚Üí 5V** for the MLX90614 wiring. That is acceptable for many GY-906 breakouts,but check your exact breakout‚Äôs 
datasheet. If your breakout‚Äôs logic lines are NOT 3.3V-tolerant when VDD=5V, either use 3.3V VDD or add an I2C level shifter.**

---

### üìà AD8232 (ECG)
| AD8232 Pin | ESP32 Pin | Notes |
|-----------:|:---------:|:-----|
| VDD        | 3.3V      | Power.|
| GND        | GND       | Ground.|
| OUT        | GPIO 34   | Analog ECG signal (ADC).|
| LO+        | GPIO 33   | Lead-off +|
| LO-        | GPIO 32   | Lead-off -|

---

### üîî Buzzer (Mini Piezo)
| Buzzer Pin | ESP32 Pin | Notes |
|-----------:|:---------:|:-----|
| IN (+)     | GPIO 13   | Buzzer input|
| GND        | GND       | Ground.|

---

### üîå Power & Other Notes
- **All grounds must be common** (tie module GNDs to ESP32 GND). 
- **I2C bus:** SDA = **GPIO 21**, SCL = **GPIO 22** (shared by MAX30100 and MLX90614).   
- **10¬µF capacitor** between **EN** and **GND** to help automatic USB upload/reset.

---

## Final notes & action items
1. **MLX90614 power:** confirm your exact MLX90614 breakout module. If it explicitly accepts 3.3V on VDD and the I¬≤C lines are 3.3V, **use 3.3V** to avoid level mismatches. If 
the breakout expects 5V and uses level shifting for I¬≤C, 5V per thesis is fine ‚Äî just confirm with the breakout datasheet.

